content: Can I attend this event virtually
overview: The AI Conference 2025 is an in-person event only.

content: Where is this event located
overview: The event is located at Pier 48, Mission Rock, San Francisco, CA 94158.

content: When is the event
overview: The AI Conference takes place on September 17th – 18th, 2025 beginning at 8:00 AM PST.

content: How can my company sponsor The AI Conference
overview: Visit aiconference.com/sponsors/ for all exhibitor opportunities.

content: Where can I park My Car
overview: The most up to date parking info can be found at Park Wiz.

content: How much does The AI Conference 2025 cost
overview: The conference has Early Bird pricing while supplies last; standard passes pricing is available on the registration page after launch.

content: Under what circumstances do you offer discounts
overview: Group rates are available to groups of three or more attendees registering together.

content: Do you offer discounts or complimentary passes
overview: Discounted group rates are available for groups of two or more people registering together.

content: What is the Cancellation policy
overview: The AI Conference offers refunds up to 30 days prior to an event with a 5% fee for all refunds.

content: Is there a code of conduct
overview: The code of conduct can be viewed at aiconference.com/code-of-conduct.

content: I have a press, vendor, or speaker pass. What now
overview: The AI Conference will send emails with information needed to navigate the event.

content: Can I present at the conference
overview: Submissions for this year’s conference speakers will open soon.

content: How do I get a press pass
overview: Members of the press can apply for a media pass shortly.

content: Who will be speaking at the conference
overview: The conference features 2 days, 4 tracks, and 85+ speakers.

content: How long will presentations be
overview: Presentations will include keynote presentations lasting 40 minutes and featured contributors lasting 20 minutes.

content: What topics will be covered
overview: Topics include AGI development, Foundation Models, Generative AI, Neural Architectures, AI Infrastructure, Ethics, and more.

content: Are there multiple presentation areas
overview: There are 4 main areas including presentation halls, a vendor area, and networking areas.

content: Which hotels are near the event
overview: Hotels near the event include Luma Hotel San Francisco, Hotel VIA, SoMa House, and Hotel Fiona.

content: Using the Circle App
overview: This section introduces the Circle App.

content: The Home Screen
overview: Introduction to the Home Screen of the application.

content: From the home screen, you can find a list of all Circle devices by tapping the devices icon in the top right portion of the screen.
overview: Instructions on how to access the list of Circle devices from the home screen.

content: From the profile screen, you can find a list of all assigned devices by selecting devices.
overview: Instructions on how to access assigned devices from the profile screen.

content: Tap on any device from the device list to see the device settings.
overview: Instructions on how to view device settings by tapping on a device.

content: The assigned profile can be edited by tapping the text.
overview: Information on how to edit the assigned profile of a device.

content: The device name can be edited by tapping the text.
overview: Information on how to edit the device name.

content: The manufacturer and device ID can help you identify the device.
overview: Details on the manufacturer and device ID for identification purposes.

content: If it's a kid device with the Circle App installed and configured, you'll see the VPN status.
overview: Information on VPN status for kid devices.

content: The option to remove device deletes this device from Circle.
overview: Information on how to remove a device from Circle.

content: If you don't want to manage this device with Circle, set it to unmanaged.
overview: Instructions on how to set a device to unmanaged.

content: A pause button is available just for this single device.
overview: Information on the pause button feature for individual devices.

content: The dashboard is where your family can check their online time for the day.
overview: Description of the dashboard's purpose for checking online time.

content: If you've assigned a family member's device to a profile, they can use the dashboard from the Circle App or a web browser.
overview: Instructions on how family members can access the dashboard.

content: On the dashboard, you'll see information for the various Circle features you've enabled for that family member.
overview: Overview of the information displayed on the dashboard for family members.

content: There's a general profile card, where you can see the device name associated with Circle.
overview: Information about the general profile card on the dashboard.

content: Push notifications let your family members know about changes to their Internet access throughout the day from Circle.
overview: Description of push notifications related to Internet access changes.

content: They'll be notified about Circle features like Pause, Time Limits, Focus Times, Bedtimes, and more.
overview: Details on the types of notifications family members will receive.

content: Parental controls right at your fingertips
overview: Introduction to the parental control features offered.

content: Simplify how you manage your family's online screen time
overview: Explanation of how the features help manage online screen time.

content: Circle's features let you set limits, filter content, and keep tabs on every connected device
overview: Details on the specific functionalities of Circle's parental control features.

content: Set online content filters that match each family member's age and interests. When setting a filter, you first must select a filter level as a starting place, which you can always customize to be the right fit for each family member.
overview: Introduction to setting online content filters for family members.

content: Grants access to kid-safe experiences like the education category but filters out content not appropriate for children most restrictive level.
overview: Description of the Kid filter level.

content: Grants access to most general-use platforms and categories without mature or adult-oriented content.
overview: Description of the Teen filter level.

content: Grants access to nearly all platforms categories and apps though explicit content is filtered out by default.
overview: Description of the Adult filter level.

content: Means that Circle won't filter content track usage or history or limit time online for any assigned devices.
overview: Description of the None filter level.

content: After you select a filter level you can customize it by setting content to allowed not allowed or unmanaged by tapping the text-box across from the platform or category name.
overview: Instructions on customizing filter settings.

content: Content from this source is available and tracked by Circle.
overview: Information about allowed content.

content: Internet traffic is allowed to freely come and go from this site even if Circle is set on Pause Bedtime or Focus Time. Traffic to any unmanaged site does not count toward Time Limits.
overview: Details on unmanaged sites and internet traffic.

content: Tapping the Custom Sites section on the right lets you create a filter setting for an individual site. Follow the steps to type in the name of the site and pick a filter setting for it.
overview: Instructions for creating custom site filters.

content: When enabled enforces an optional YouTube setting to filter out potentially mature videos and livestreaming.
overview: Description of the YouTube restricted setting.

content: Limit online time for individual apps sites or categories You can set limits by day category of content or for individual apps and sites
overview: This section explains the purpose of setting time limits for online activities.

content: Tap on a profile from the home screen then select Time Limits from the feature list Turn Time Limits on by tapping the enable switch in the top right Set an all-day cap by tapping Daily Time Limit at the top of the list Set an all-day cap by tapping the selector beneath the profile picture Create an alternate schedule for certain days of the week by tapping the add weekend icon at the top of the screen Manage time as a reward instead of giving a set limit every day by selecting by reward only for a Time Limit
overview: This section provides instructions on how to set time limits for online activities.

content: Make late-night scrolling a thing of the past Bedtime shuts off Internet access for every device assigned to a profile through the night so everybody in your family can get the sleep they need without distraction You can even set a separate weekend Bedtime
overview: This section describes the Bedtime feature that restricts internet access during the night.

content: When setting Bedtime the day of the week represents the night a Bedtime begins Typical weekday Bedtime spans Sunday to Thursday with weekend nights on Friday and Saturday
overview: This section explains the typical schedule for setting Bedtime.

content: Tap on a profile from the home screen then select Bedtime from the feature list Turn Bedtime on by tapping the enable switch in the top right Set the Bedtime by tapping on the days to toggle them on or off and tap Bedtime and Awake times to set the clock Tap add weekend to set an alternate Bedtime for certain days of the week Press save to finish
overview: This section provides instructions on how to set the Bedtime feature.

content: Create a customized screen time schedule that benefits everyone in your family. Preset time offline for the important moments like practicing piano or dinner with the family.
overview: Instructions for creating a family screen time schedule.

content: Tap on a profile from the home screen, then select Focus Time from the feature list. Tap the down arrow or select from your existing Focus Time below. Set the Focus Time by typing in a name for the Focus Time, selecting which days you'd like to activate, and scroll through the start and end times to set the clock. Press done to finish, then save to keep all your changes for this profile.
overview: Steps to set up Focus Time for a profile.

content: Pause the Internet with the tap of a button for individual family members or the whole house. Tapping again will unpause to resume Internet. Unmanaged devices will always maintain Internet access.
overview: Explanation of how to pause the Internet for family members or the entire house.

content: To pause all Circle devices at once, press the pause button on the home screen, then confirm. Press the same button again to unpause.
overview: Instructions for pausing all Circle devices simultaneously.

content: To pause a family member, tap on their profile from the home screen, then tap the pause button in the top-left corner of the screen. Press the same button again to unpause.
overview: Steps to pause Internet access for a specific family member.

content: To pause a single device, tap the devices icon in the top-right of the home screen, then tap on a device from the list, then press the pause button on the bottom of the screen. Press the same button again to unpause.
overview: Instructions for pausing a specific device.

content: Find the current location for a family member's mobile devices. To use Location, the devices you want to locate must have the Circle App and VPN installed with location services enabled. Notification services must also be enabled on the parents' and kids' devices. Additionally, Location will only work once the mobile device is assigned to the kid's profile that you wish to location.
overview: Instructions for using the Location feature to find a family member's mobile device.

content: To locate a family member's device, tap on a profile from the home screen, then select location from the feature list. You might have to pick from a list of devices to locate. Wait for Circle to locate the device. When the device has been found, you'll see a marker on the map. At the bottom of the screen, you'll see the time when the location was received. Tap refresh to see their location again.
overview: Steps to locate a family member's device using the Circle App.

content: Locating a device will only work if location services are enabled on the device you are locating, and Circle will notify you if this is the reason a device cannot be located.
overview: Requirement for location services to be enabled for successful device locating.

content: Circle does not store a history of previous locations.
overview: Information about Circle's policy on storing location history.

content: History displays a chronological list of sites viewed by a profile. Toggle between Filtered and Visited to see which sites were prevented or accessed.
overview: Description of the History feature that shows sites viewed by a family member.

content: To see a family member's History, tap on a profile from the home screen, then select History in the feature list. Select visited to see sites that a family member accessed. Toggle over to filtered to see sites that Circle blocked because of a family member's filter settings.
overview: Instructions for viewing a family member's browsing history in the Circle App.

content: To take action on a History entry, tap on it and select from the following options: Visit website, which opens your web browser and takes you to the home page of the site, Set as allowed, Set as not allowed, Set as unmanaged. You can edit any of these custom filters by selecting Filter from the profile features list, then tapping custom filter on the bottom of the screen.
overview: Options available for taking action on a history entry in the Circle App.

content: Compare time online today last week or months past while viewing the total time spent online per category and platform
overview: Instructions on comparing online time across different periods and categories

content: See a list of sites and platforms by tapping on a category A pop-up menu will allow you to take action on a particular category that contributed total online time
overview: How to view sites and platforms and take action on categories contributing to online time

content: You may notice total online time does not always match the sum of usage from visible categories This is because each platform's algorithm is unique and may contribute differently to active screen time versus background traffic
overview: Explanation of discrepancies in total online time due to platform algorithms

content: To see a family member's Usage Select Usage in the feature list
overview: Steps to view a family member's online usage

content: At the top of the screen you can select between usage by day week or month
overview: Options for viewing usage data by different time frames

content: Next you'll see a summary of total time Below that you can scroll from the current period and into past usage
overview: Viewing summary of total time and scrolling through past usage

content: Take action on a Usage entry by following the same steps outlined above for History
overview: Instructions for taking action on usage entries

content: In addition to the popular apps and websites visible by default Circle can help you manage IOOs more through Usage
overview: Circle's capability to manage IOOs through usage data

content: Rewards are an easy way to send family members extra online time for an individual day Rewards expire at midnight so original time limits are reset the following day
overview: Information about rewards for extra online time and their expiration

content: To send a Reward Tap on a profile from the home screen then tap the star in the top right corner or select Rewards from the feature list
overview: Steps to send a reward to a family member

content: Pick from three types of rewards Extend Time Limit Late Bedtime or Disable Focus Time
overview: Types of rewards available for family members

content: Set the Reward based on the existing settings and press send to finish
overview: Instructions for setting and sending a reward

content: To edit or cancel a Reward Tap on a profile from the home screen and select Rewards from the feature list
overview: Steps to edit or cancel a reward

content: To edit a Reward tap the edit existing rewards button to make the appropriate changes
overview: Instructions for editing an existing reward

content: To cancel a Reward tap the edit existing rewards button and swipe to delete it from the list
overview: Instructions for canceling a reward

content: Circle Home Plus device
overview: Introduction to the Circle Home Plus device

content: Circle Home Plus pairs directly with your router and inspects all the non-encrypted Internet traffic coming through your home network. You won't need to install software or adjust settings on your devices to manage them.
overview: Description of Circle Home Plus functionality and ease of use.

content: If you don't have a Circle Home Plus open the Circle App and press get Circle Home Plus from the home screen menu
overview: Instructions for obtaining Circle Home Plus through the Circle App
